In tmux, hit the prefix ctrl+b (my modified prefix is ctrl+a) and then:
                      Toggle mouse with prefix + m
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
-                              Sessions                               -
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

C-f find session
C-c create session
s  list sessions
$  name session

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
-                               Windows                               -
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

c   create window
w   list windows
C-h previous-window
C-l next-window
Tab last-window
f  find window
,  name window
&  kill window

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
-                                Panes                                -
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

h  move left
j  move down
k  move up
l  move right
_  vertical split
-  horizontal split
o  swap panes
x  kill pane
q (Show pane numbers, when the numbers show up type the key to goto that pane)
+  break pane into window (e.g. to select text by mouse to copy)
-  restore pane from window
⍽  space - toggle between layouts
z toggle pane zoom
{ (Move the current pane left)
} (Move the current pane right)
> swap current pane with the next one
< swap current pane with the previous one

# pane resizing
H Left resize
J Down resize
K Up resize
L Right Resize
